What does the Bible say about Ethnicity?
Large group of people according to class, cultural origin, background, distinct people groups.

!! There are Different Ethnicities
* Moses Marrying a Cushite Woman, Numbers 12
* Rahab the Amorite in the Line of Jesus, Matthew 1:5
* Ruth the Moabitess in the Line of Jesus, Matthew 1:5

As history unfolds, there are different ethnicity. But you will be surprised how many did not understand. The fact that God has split various 

Moses marrying a Cushite woman in Africa in Number 12. Matthew 1:5 we have Rahab and Ruth. We have clear Biblical commands of how to treat Christians of different ethnicities. Tower of Bable does not say how one ought to behave but rather it accounts the pride of man.

People have made an ethnicity centered philosophy. Revelation 7:9. There are so many different cultures and since ethnicities exist in heaven, it must therefore be important.

Everything around us, when in Christ, is rubbish. Philippians 3:8 this Word is after Paul boasts about what he had. John 3:30 "He must increase, but I must decrease."

Ethnicity is a big thing but it should never come close for your love for Christ. Be careful when you try to emphasize the problem of ethnicity.

1 Corinthians 12:12 cf. Romans 12 cf, Ephesians 4 cf. You see that the notion is focused on function and gifted-ness.

Ethnicity does exist in heaven but that is not the main point of those verses.
Revelations 7:9-10, they are coming together is on the worship of God and on the lamb. They are all clothed in white clothes and palm branches. The Uniformity and Unity of the body of Christ is really the point.

!! There is But One Christian People Group (Genos)
Fundamentally we are one, united, and together. That is the emphasis of Scripture time and time again.

<<<
But you are a chosen race, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people for his own possession, that you may proclaim the excellencies of him who called you out of darkness into his marvelous light.
<<<
''1 Peter 2:9''

We are not a dozen Christian nations, but we are one race. It doesn't matter what we look like on the outside. We are one people and one race. We are bound together by the foundation in Jesus Christ, by which everything else is measured. There are even more cases.

<<<
For in one Spirit we were all baptized into one body - Jews or Greeks, slaves or free - and all were made to drink of one Spirit.
<<<
