!!! Love Impartially
As Christians we put on love as a way to promote Christian harmony.

In the world we have people telling us that love is doing what people want. Other people are telling us that love is affirming people's life choices. We just can't do that.

Bible gives us examples of how to love people in different ethnicities.

<<<
If you really fulfill the royal law according to the Scripture, "You shall love your neighbor as yourself," you are doing well. But if you show partiality, you are committing sin and are convicted by the law as transgressors.
<<<
''James 2:8-9''

<<<
From now on, therefore, we regard no one according to the flesh. Even though we once regarded Christ according to the flesh, we regard him thus no longer. Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, he is a new creation. The old has passed away; behold, the new has come.
